Author: John | Safe#1403
Content:
The Safe core contributors team is relatively small, and we cannot keep up with the volume of developer questions we receive using a chat model. For this reason, we decided to move our developer support to Ethereum Stack Exchange.
By doing this, we will create a knowledge base for Safe products and developer tools, indexed by search engines, making life easier for developers who will build on top of the Safe protocol in the future!

**Please post your question here -**
https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/tagged/gnosis-safe
Please be as detailed as possible and don’t forget to add `gnosis-safe` tag to your question 🙏 StackOverflow’s guide to asking a good question may be helpful:
https://stackoverflow.com/help/how-to-ask

**Types of dev support questions and where to ask:**
- How do I? -- Ask in Stack Exchange with `gnosis-safe` tag
- I got this error, why? -- Ask in Stack Exchange with `gnosis-safe` tag
- I got this error and I’m sure it’s a bug -- file an issue in the relevant Github repo within https://github.com/safe-global
- I have an idea/request -- file an issue in the relevant Github repo within https://github.com/safe-global
- Why do you? -- discuss this in relevant Discord channel
- Wen will you? -- same as Why do you

Stay Safe out there 🔐
